article.headline: Long Beach St. 72, Boise St. 62
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. -- T.J. Robinson had 18 points and 13 rebounds Tuesday night and Long Beach State beat Boise State 72-62. James Ennis contributed 16 points and six assists, and Eugene Phelps added 11 points as the 49ers (3-1) bounced back from a loss to San Diego State. Long Beach State won at No. 17 Pittsburgh last week. The 49ers led by 23 points with 5 1/2 minutes to go before the Broncos closed the game on a 17-4 run. Freshman Anthony Drmic led Boise State (3-1) with 20 points, including five 3-pointers. Kenny Buckner scored 12 of his 14 points in the first half for the Broncos, whose only lead was after the game's first basket.
